shared_text:
Louisiana Department of Education
September 8 at 8:30 AM ¬∑

Louisiana is reopening the Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) program for families who did not apply in May and June. Families of children who receive free or reduced-price school meals may be eligible to receive financial benefits for meals missed in 2019-2020 when schools closed due to the pandemic. Apply from September 8 at 8 a.m. to September 29 at 5 p.m. These one-time benefits total $285 per child of families who were eligible for free and reduced-price meals during the entire closure last spring. Parents who started receiving free and reduced-price school meals in May will receive $91.20 per eligible child. The online application is simple. The information submitted must exactly match the information on file with the school system in order for the application to successfully submit. #louisianabelieves

https://pebt.doe.louisiana.gov/PublicApps/SNP/

IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT

Beginning this week, Grab and Go lunch and breakfasts will be Mondays and Thursdays, instead of Mondays and Wednesdays. We are happy to announce this change is because students will now be receiving meals for 7 days instead of 5. Pick-up locations will continue to be at BHS and Byrd Avenue schools. At BHS, the pick-up spot will be behind the gym and cafeteria. There will be tables set up for pick up. At Byrd Avenue, the pick-up will be in front of the school.

post_text:
To our students, community members, parents, and the Bogalusa High School Class of 2020:

This Friday, April 17, from 8:15-8:45 pm, please join us and pass along Avenue B in front of the school and the baseball and football fields. At this time, we will honor and celebrate our seniors and their pending graduation with a show of support and encouragement with posters and banners along the fence.

No one will be allowed to stop or get out of their vehicles as we abide by social distancing expectations.

Parents, we ask that you create banners or posters to hang along the fence in front of the school.
Administration will hang these for you; you may drop them by the school office Friday between 7:00-11:00.

We cannot wait to see you there!

Bogalusa High School
March 7 at 2:58 PM ¬∑

59 BHS 9-12th graders attended District Literary Rally at Southeastern Louisiana University today. Their teachers selected them as top students in their subject area to compete on tests where they were ranked according to their scores among other students from all over our district. BHS is proud to say eight students placed in their tested subject with three of those scoring in the top tier of testers. These students are now eligible to move on to state competition. We are so proud of all of these students and their accomplishments!!!
